      "text": "The cleanest freedom comes from making \"never another puff\" not a rule you strain against but a fact you've accepted, like \"I don't eat glass.\" You're not constantly resisting glass; you simply don't consider it food. Aim for that relationship with the cigarette. When the \"just one\" thought floats up — and it will, occasionally, for a while — you don't debate it. You recognise it instantly as the trap's last and most cunning lie, and you let it drift past unanswered. A thought you don't engage has no power to move your hand."
